api-1  | What excites you about a career in engineering/technology? Why do you think your abilities and skills are a good fit for
api-1  | Plaksha's B.Tech program?
api-1  | From a young age, I’ve been fascinated by how things work—whether it's the logic behind mobile apps, the science in smart devices, or the
api-1  | innovation that powers everyday life. What excites me most about engineering and technology is the ability to solve real-world problems
api-1  | using creativity and logic. It's not just about building machines or writing code—it's about designing solutions that can create meaningful
api-1  | impact. The ever-evolving nature of tech, combined with its potential to transform industries from healthcare to climate, makes this field
api-1  | incredibly exciting for me.
api-1  | I believe my curiosity, collaborative mindset, and eagerness to learn make me a strong fit for Plaksha’s B.Tech program. I enjoy working on
api-1  | projects, asking questions, and applying what I learn to practical challenges. I also have a keen interest in interdisciplinary learning—blending
api-1  | tech with design, data, and human behavior—which I understand is core to Plaksha’s approach. What draws me most to Plaksha is its focus
api-1  | on innovation, entrepreneurship, and societal impact. I’m excited by the opportunity to learn from faculty, mentors, and peers who are
api-1  | passionate about building a better future through technology. Plaksha’s hands-on curriculum, values-driven mission, and emphasis on
api-1  | leadership resonate deeply with my aspirations.
api-1  | Share a time when you contributed to a project or activity that positively affected your school or community. What
api-1  | challenges did you face, and what did you learn about leadership and perseverance?
api-1  | Having grown up with a pet dog, I’ve developed a deep sense of empathy and care for animals. That personal connection inspired me to take
api-1  | action when I noticed several stray dogs in my neighborhood struggling with hunger, injuries, and neglect. I initiated a small project with a
api-1  | few classmates to support these animals by organizing feeding drives, arranging basic medical aid through local NGOs, and spreading
api-1  | awareness about responsible and humane treatment of strays.
api-1  | One of the major challenges was addressing concerns from some residents who were initially uncomfortable with our activities. There were
api-1  | worries about safety and cleanliness. Instead of giving up, I took the time to understand their perspective and created a small awareness
api-1  | campaign. We shared how caring for strays through sterilization and regular feeding could actually make the community safer. We also made
api-1  | sure to clean up after every feeding and involved local animal welfare volunteers to lend credibility to our efforts.
api-1  | This experience taught me that leadership is as much about listening and empathy as it is about action. It showed me how
api-1  | perseverance—combined with teamwork and a clear sense of purpose—can gradually change mindsets and make a difference. It also
api-1  | reinforced that even small initiatives, when pursued with sincerity, can have a positive and lasting impact.
api-1  | Is there anything else which you would like to share with us
api-1  | which would help us understand you better?
api-1  | Yes
api-1  | Description
api-1  | I’ve been raised in a home where both my parents are entrepreneurs, and that has had a profound influence on how I think and what I aspire
api-1  | to become. From an early age, I was exposed to conversations about solving real problems, taking risks, and creating value. This
api-1  | environment taught me to be curious, independent, and driven by purpose.
api-1  | Watching them build businesses from scratch showed me the impact one can make through innovation and perseverance. It also inspired my
api-1  | vision—to one day become an entrepreneur who uses technology to solve meaningful challenges in society, whether in education,
api-1  | sustainability, or healthcare.
api-1  | What excites me about Plaksha is its mission to develop tech leaders with a strong sense of societal impact. I believe it’s the perfect place for
api-1  | me to grow my skills, broaden my perspective, and begin a journey where I can create solutions that truly matter.
